It sure looks like Obamacare is driving down the uninsured rate
The downturn in the uninsured rate coincides with the start of the largest expansion of health insurance coverage in more than five decades, which is more commonly known as Obamacare. The evidence is pretty overwhelming at this point that Obamacare has driven down the uninsured rate. Data from  , the    ,   and the   all have similar findings. Namely, that millions more people have insurance than before Obamacare's insurance expansion. Yes, Gallup definitely does scale the Y-axis to make the downturn look quite dramatic. But regardless of data visualization decisions, the evidence that Obamacare means fewer people without insurance is becoming pretty overwhelming. Get our newsletter in your inbox twice a week. 